ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I believe my partner is a good parent
Notes: 0 = Not true of us; 2 = A little bit true of us; 4 = Somewhat true of us; 6 = Very true of us

ElementDescription: My relationship with my partner is stronger now than before we had a child
Notes: 0 = Not true of us; 2 = A little bit true of us; 4 = Somewhat true of us; 6 = Very true of us

ElementDescription: My partner asks my opinion on issues related to parenting
Notes: 0 = Not true of us; 2 = A little bit true of us; 4 = Somewhat true of us; 6 = Very true of us

ElementDescription: My partner pays a great deal of attention to our child
Notes: 0 = Not true of us; 2 = A little bit true of us; 4 = Somewhat true of us; 6 = Very true of us

ElementDescription: How often in a typical week, when all 3 of you are together, do you find yourself in a mildly tense or sarcastic interchange with your partner?
Notes: 0 = Never; 2 = Sometimes; 4 = Often; 6 = Very often

ElementDescription: My partner likes to play with our child and then leave dirty work to me
Notes: 6 = Not true of us; 4 = A little bit true of us; 2 = Somewhat true of us; 0 = Very true of us

ElementDescription: My partner and I have the same goals for our child
Notes: 0 = Not true of us; 2 = A little bit true of us; 4 = Somewhat true of us; 6 = Very true of us

ElementDescription: My partner still wants to do his or her own thing instead of being a responsible parent
Notes: 6 = Not true of us; 4 = A little bit true of us; 2 = Somewhat true of us; 0 = Very true of us

Notes: 0 = Not true of us; 2 = A little bit true of us; 4 = Somewhat true of us; 6 = Very true of us

ElementDescription: My partner and I have different ideas about how to raise our child
Notes: 6 = Not true of us; 4 = A little bit true of us; 2 = Somewhat true of us; 0 = Very true of us

ElementDescription: How often in a typical week, when all 3 of you are together, do you argue with your partner about your child, in the child's presence
Notes: 0 = Never; 2 = Sometimes; 4 = Often; 6 = Very often
